result.execSummary:
The defendant Victoria L Soulier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Victoria L Soulier in court with attorney Adam C Essling.  Defendant Victoria L Soulier in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Pursuant to negotiations Counts 2 & 3 are dismissed but read in for the purpose of sentencing.  The repeater enhancer on Count 1 is dismissed.

As to Count 1:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Jury trial of 05/19/2014 is vacated.    Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 40.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 14, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
Same conditions to apply.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.  Bail motion by the state argued and granted by the Court.  Bail $10,000.00
